<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ache1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ache,</orth> subst. pain, especially a chronical pain caused by inveterate ills: <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.1.93" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 1, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.3.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 3, 105</bibl>. Pronounced like the name of the letter H, <bibl n="shak. ado 3.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 4, 56</bibl>, and therefore dissyll. in the plural: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 370</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.257" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 257</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.202" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 202</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>